Reasoning: The paper presents a method for planning and executing multi-step manipulation tasks using robotic agents in cluttered tabletop environments. This involves learning dynamics models at different levels of temporal resolution and using cascaded variational inference to generate effective action sequences. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the method involves processing high-dimensional observations, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of cascaded variational inference to model dynamics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
